```

The loop runs from `k=1` to `k<=frame_length+3`, which means `k` can be `frame_length+3` at the maximum. When `k = frame_length+3`, the code writes to `ext[k-1]` which is `ext[frame_length+2]`.

So the `ext` array needs to have size at least `frame_length+3` to accommodate indices from `0` to `frame_length+2`.

Currently in `phy_threegpplte_turbo_decoder_scalar`, the arrays are allocated as:
```c
short ext[n],ext2[n];
```

But `n` here is the coded block size, which is passed as `frame_length` to `log_map_s`. So `ext` and `ext2` need to be `n+3` instead of `n`.

The fix is straightforward: change the allocation size from `n` to `n+3`.

